SIMPLE: buttonhole
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Buttonhole
<hw>But"ton*hole`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The hole or
loop in which a button is caught.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Buttonhole</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Buttonhole
<hw>But"ton*hole`</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To hold at the button or
buttonhole; to detain in conversation to weariness; to bore; <as>as, he
<ex>buttonholed</ex> me a quarter of an hour</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Buttonmold</ent>⟦br⟧
